The paper proposes a novel reinforcement learning approach for answering complex questions, which involves multiple entities and relations. This falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR), which are covered by cs.CL and cs.IR respectively. The use of reinforcement learning also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (AI), which is covered by cs.AI. The approach involves learning a policy to dynamically decide which sub-question to answer, which involves balancing between risk and utility. This suggests a focus on machine learning (ML) and decision making, which are covered by cs.LG and cs.SD respectively.
